photo.title: Belt of Venus

description._content:
If you like to be chained up & beaten by a leather clad dominatrix, or even just enjoy a good spanking - you could be forgiven for feeling a frisson of excitement at the mention of Belt of Venus - after all Venus is the goddess of love.
 Unfortunately I discovered this week that Belt of Venus is a term for something much more humdrum - the pink arch seen above the blue band of the Earth's shadow as witnessed here behind Coit tower.
 Had to do this long panorama of evening light on the buildings on Nob hill - didn't feel I could cut out Coit tower or the Art Deco buildings on Fisherman's wharf?
 Wanted to wait for a blue hour shot but was getting that look of impatience from my wife that says it's dinner time.

Thanks to Everyone who took the trouble to view, comment or fave.

photo.title: Coit Tower

description._content:
Coit Tower from Russian Hill.  It is a 210-foot, Art Deco, concrete column on Telegraph Hill in San Francisco, CA.  The tower was built in 1933.

The view from the top is spectacular!

description._content: Over the past 49 years we've lived across the bay, we've seen the City's skyline change.  In the beginning, the most recognizable features were The B of A building (a brooding hulk), the Ferry Building tower and this, Coit Tower.  Now,  well they are still visible but dwarfed.  San Spade would not know where he was.  San Francisco; June, 2016.

photo.title: Full Moon Line Up with Coit Tower

description._content: This was a full moon-set I took on Sunday morning. I used PlanIt app to calculate the camera spot, so the setting full moon will align with coit tower at some point. I used my second camera to take a time-lapse to record the whole process. And here is a short timelapse consist of 200 pictures before and after my final shot: youtu.be/o9fsEZ00Coc There are so many alternations on full moon pictures right now in photography community, since photoshop app is making the alternation much easier than before. However, I feel more joyful and satisfactory when I am doing the real full moon shooting and when everything is moving as my prediction.

photo.title: Life Around Washington Square Park

description._content:
If Columbus Avenue is the artery of North Beach neighborhood in San Francisco, then Washington Square Park is the heart.  Besides some nice small restaurants and shops, the picturesque Saints Peter and Paul Cathedral (not in view) and Coit Tower (seen here) are beautiful backdrops of this urban park.  You'll always see people laying around, picnicking, and doing other activities (such as playing frisbees).

Processed to look like shot on Fuji Superia Reala 35mm film, but warmer like Kodak Portra 400.

description._content: Coit Tower, also known as the Lillian Coit Memorial Tower, is a 210-foot (64 m) tower in the Telegraph Hill neighborhood of San Francisco, California. The tower, in the city's Pioneer Park, was built in 1933 using Lillie Hitchcock Coit's bequest to beautify the city of San Francisco. It was added to the National Register of Historic Places on January 29, 2008

photo.title: i-Moon

description._content:
The 2016 Warriors are making another bid to become back to back World Champions. Tonight, Coit Tower and the Full Moon were the players on this court. A ton of photographers were at hand to enjoy this great time of the year when the top of the moon sits right above Coit Tower. 

Oh what a wonderful life it is! 

Single shot. No blending. 100% Natural. No artificial flavors or preservatives.

photo.title: Collected Vision

description._content:
The weather didn't cooperate tonight trying to align the moon with Coit Tower in San Francisco,. There was a glimpse of the moon as it was peeking out of the fog/clouds and just enough to align it to my intended target. 

The clouds were a mix blessing. On the one hand I wanted it to be clear, but on the other hand, it yielded some pretty colors.

photo.title: San Francisco Panostack

description._content: A monstrously l-o-n-g panorama formatted in a stack so it can be traditionally framed.  There is a bit of overlap at each end so you can see about 180 degrees of San Francisco skyline from the Bay Bridge to the north end of the Golden Gate. Made from 42 separate high-resolution images.  That spec in the sky in the bottom frame is a helicopter.  The complete panorama is about 18.5 feet long! (@300dpi)  Available up to 78x50 inches without logo/watermarks.

photo.title: Coit Tower

description._content: This is Coit Tower, a famous land mark in San Francisco City. If you’ve seen, bought, or received a post card from San Francisco, you’ve probably seen this building. What people probably do not know unless they live in the San Francisco Bay Area its that the tower is built in the form of a fire hose nozzle. Coit Tower was built to honor the firemen who lost their lives in the great San Francisco Fire.
